```

## Registration Progress Indicator

Use a segmented progress indicator:

- 4 segments;
- first segment active;
- remaining segments inactive;
- active segment uses accent gradient;
- inactive segments are muted;
- rounded segment ends;
- subtle glow on active segment.

Example:

```css
.progress {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
  gap: 8px;
  width: 360px;
  max-width: 100%;
}

.progress-segment {
  height: 5px;
  border-radius: 999px;
  background: rgba(160, 170, 210, 0.20);
}

.progress-segment.active {
  background: linear-gradient(90deg, #7C8CFF 0%, #3F6BFF 100%);
  box-shadow: 0 0 18px rgba(91, 124, 255, 0.45);
}
```

## Layout Rules

- Do not create cramped forms.
- Do not over-expand the card.
- Do not align elements randomly.
- Keep form width consistent.
- Keep input and button widths aligned.
- Keep vertical rhythm consistent.
- Desktop must look very close to the reference.
